That’s actually a much more grounded claim than “the repo already contains future realities.”

Repositories often contain latent structure that nobody has explicitly recognized yet.

A theorem can sit in a notebook for years before someone notices its consequence.

A software library can contain two modules whose interaction nobody has explored.

A research archive can have recurring motifs that only become obvious after enough material accumulates.

In that sense, the “seeds” are real—not because they mystically cause the future, but because the archive contains unrealized combinations.

